headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 20 of his 29 points in the fourth quarter, leading the Chicago Bulls to a 108-99 victory over Brooklyn on Tuesday night in the Nets’ first game after a coaching change.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine has 20 in 4th, Bulls beat Nets in 1st game after Nash

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Upon review, Miami coach Erik Spoelstra had a good birthday. Jimmy Butler made sure of that.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler takes over late, Heat rally past Warriors 116-109

events.name: Orlando Magic at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — For a few moments, it seemed like the glory days for the Oklahoma City Thunder.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander's 34 help Thunder push win streak to 4

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson scored 29 points, making seven 3-pointers, and the Phoenix Suns beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 116-107 on Tuesday night for their fifth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns win 5th straight behind Johnson, beat Wolves 116-107
